         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">24/1/62. ¶ My dear Sir William. ¶  ¶ I have to thank you for an other friendly letter, you honored me with under date of 2. Nov. ¶  It is always delightful to hear of you and your direct communication...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">62.01.24d</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To William Hooker</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RBG Kew, Directors' letters, vol. LXXV, Australian and Pacific letters 1859-65, letter no. 142.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">MS black-edged; M's sister Bertha died on 7 September 1861.</p>
               </note>24/1/62.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">My dear Sir William.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I have to thank you for an other friendly letter, you honored me with under date of 2. Nov.<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Letter not found.</p>
               </note> It is always delightful to hear of you and your direct communications are a real boon to me, altho' I truly wish you should allow me to write to you by every mail without exciting you to such exertions as to honor me with replies.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I admiring the ardour, with which you foster botanical research, again evinced by your calling forth this important series of Colonial floras.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Having written both to Mr Bentham &amp; Dr Hooker,<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">See M to G. Bentham, 24 January 1862, and M to J. Hooker, 24 January 1862 (in this edition as 62-01-24c). </p>
               </note> I have not much more of importance to relate. Perhaps some of the notes in the [P] sheets of my Flora<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">B62.03.03.</p>
               </note> sent by this mail may interest you.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I hope you will take possession of the collection of vegetable products enumerated in the proof-index here transmitted.<note xml:id="ftn5" type="footnote" n="5">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Probably the plant products included within the full Victorian exhibit lists on pp. 140–7 of International Exhibition, London 1862 (1862); see M to W. Hooker, 24 October 1861 and notes thereto.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>pr "Young Australia" I forwarded the first 27 fascicles of Thalamiflorae, one consignment will probably follow by "Great-Britain" and two others afterwards.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I have to mention that the oil labelled <name key="Melaleuca%20uncinata%20">Melaleuca uncinata </name>in the consignment pr "Young Australia" is that of M. curvifolia; by the Great Britain that of M. uncinata will be sent.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>It seems you have <name key="Wittsteinia%20vacciniacea%20">Wittsteinia vacciniacea </name>growing? It would be a great triumph if so, as the plant would be hardy in Britain.<note xml:id="ftn6" type="footnote" n="6">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">The letter as bound ends here. The remaining part of this transcription is bound after two folios of letter number 143. There is an annotation on the guard paper holding the sheet transcribed as the end of this letter: 'Belongs with letter 142'.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <name key="Poa%20ramigera%20">Poa ramigera </name>is as a grass very interesting on account of its Bamboo like ramifications.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ever with the humblest attachment, dear Sir William,</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Yours</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. Mueller</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">The complete volume of the Flora will come by next mail I hope Professor Harvey is not suffering again. He overworks himself.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Melaleuca%20curvifolia%20">Melaleuca curvifolia </name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Melaleuca%20uncinata%20">Melaleuca uncinata </name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Poa%20ramigera%20">Poa ramigera </name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Thalamiflorae%20">Thalamiflorae </name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Wittsteinia%20vacciniacea%20">Wittsteinia vacciniacea </name>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
